UNITED STATES ex rel. Sidney COHEN, Relator-Appellant, v. Raymond J. MULLIGAN. U. S. Marshal, etc., Respondent-Appellee. No. 250. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 23, 1933. Boehm & Zeiger, of New York City (Louis Boehm and Harry M. Edelstein, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Thomas E. Dewey, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Russell H. Dorr, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open court.
